To render individual figures: go into the page directory 000,
and run ../fig 000.

Figures are rendered in groups and placed in a text file.
These have to arguments: the page index, and the name of
the figure to use for filename output. the filename of this
path is then associated with a graph entry in graphs.txt.
When generate.sh script is run, it will read entries from
the figs file entry, and render them in a folder called "figs".
Figures will also append dagzet data to the generated dz file
associated with the graph.

So, to render a figure in this ecosystem, add it to a
list of figures associated with a graph, and it will be created
when the generate script is run. If no such list exists for
that graph, make a list in this folder, then add that list filepath
to the appropriate column in graphs.txt.
